The paper proposes a novel object proposal algorithm that improves proposal localization quality while maintaining computational efficiency. This is a problem commonly addressed in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic modeling and parameter learning, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
